logs:
 @WiseOwl71, you're absolutely right. This isn't about supporting a lifestyle, it's about providing a service. A baker shouldn't be able to pick and choose who they serve based on their personal beliefs. If they can't do their job without discriminating, maybe they should find a different line of work.

@QueenOfChaos, you're right that this is the internet, but that doesn't mean we should throw respect out the window. We can have passionate discussions without resorting to personal attacks. And @DarkShadow333, bringing up religion and hell isn't going to help your argument. Let's stick to the facts and keep the conversation civil.

@moderator, thank you for keeping us in line. Let's all try to remember that there are real people on the other side of these screens.
